1
00:00:00,792 --> 00:00:02,544
<i>You think you can just buy us with money?</i>

2
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:05,839
<i>If it wasn't for me, you'd have been</i>
<i>dead a long time ago, Olsen!</i>

3
00:00:05,922 --> 00:00:08,967
<i>Why won't you just apologize to Olsen?</i>

4
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:12,220
<i>You side with them</i>
<i>as if they're your family!</i>

5
00:00:12,303 --> 00:00:14,931
<i>Liam and I are your family!</i>

6
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:17,559
<i>I'm your wife, Magnus!</i>

7
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:19,519
<i>Auntie Wendy. Olsen.</i>

8
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:20,478
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

9
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:21,938
<i>What Mama did was wrong.</i>

10
00:00:22,021 --> 00:00:24,774
<i>Liam, are you forgetting</i>
<i>the other thing you did to us?</i>

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:26,776
<i>What else do you want me to do?</i>
<i>Kneel in front of you?</i>

12
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:30,155
<i>Will that undo the gunshot my mother took?</i>

13
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:31,990
<i>Olsen, Liam, stop it.</i>

14
00:00:32,073 --> 00:00:35,952
<i>Can't we focus on escaping</i>
<i>from this island first?</i>

15
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,912
<i>Three people are patrolling</i>
<i>the north perimeter</i>

16
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:39,247
<i>in the villa areas. Over.</i>

17
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:40,665
<i>Do you have visual on the hostages?</i>

18
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:43,042
<i>- Command, negative.</i>
<i>- Maintain observation of the area.</i>

19
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:44,961
<i>Report any movements right away. Over.</i>

20
00:00:45,044 --> 00:00:46,588
<i>Let's go! Let's leave this island!</i>

21
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:48,381
<i>Go and save yourself.</i>

22
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>You have parents</i>
<i>who are worrying about you.</i>

23
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:51,634
<i>You and Olsen,</i>

24
00:00:51,718 --> 00:00:53,219
<i>you're my family.</i>

25
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:56,723
<i>Luna knows where the staff are.</i>
<i>We'll take as many as we can.</i>

26
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:59,309
<i>Okay. We'll get the hostages</i>
<i>in the banquet hall out.</i>

27
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,435
<i>We'll meet here after.</i>

28
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,687
<i>We'll try to look for Fin and Grandpa too.</i>

29
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:03,938
<i>- Okay.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

30
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:05,607
<i>That's the spirit!</i>

31
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:08,568
<i>- One, two--</i>
<i>- We're just wasting time. Let's go.</i>

32
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,700
[LUCAS] <i>How did Dr. Morillo,</i>
<i>his wife, and Jules Santos escape?</i>

33
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:19,954
<i>They're guarded by police, and I'm sure</i>
<i>there are police officers over there too.</i>

34
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:22,499
<i>- Put your guns down!</i>
<i>- Hands in the air!</i>

35
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:26,461
[OFFICER] <i>Confirmed, sir. Ben Bonifacio,</i>
<i>Head of Security at La Playa Roja.</i>

36
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:27,921
<i>Let them go.</i>

37
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:29,130
<i>We're here to save you.</i>

38
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:35,595
Sir, this is where the banquet hall is.

39
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:37,806
All the hostages are there.

40
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:41,059
The base of operations
of the hostage takers

41
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:43,978
is most likely in there too.

42
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:46,773
How can we get there without being caught?

43
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:51,319
Sir, every area
we'll pass through has guards.

44
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:52,529
<i>It's dangerous, sir.</i>

45
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:56,741
It'll be safer if we approach
from the sides.

46
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:58,910
We'll have more hiding spots.

47
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:02,163
Okay, let's form three groups.

48
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:06,209
The first group
will head to the north side.

49
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:09,420
The second group will head out west,

50
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:10,964
here in the lagoon area,

51
00:02:11,047 --> 00:02:15,135
and the third group
will guard the beachfront.

52
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:18,680
If anything goes wrong,
you know what to do.

53
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:20,765
- Am I clear?!
- [OFFICERS] Yes, sir!

54
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:23,268
The goal is extraction.

55
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:26,604
We need to get the survivors out alive.

56
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:29,065
We have to get them off this island.

57
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,900
- Let's move!
- Let's go! Let's go!

58
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:32,986
- [OFFICER 1] Let's go!
- [OFFICER 2] Let's move!

59
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:35,363
- [BEN] Be careful, Fin.
- Let's go, Chief!

60
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:47,750
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,133
[CLEARS THROAT]

62
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,433
Lucas just gave me a report.

63
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:07,770
Dr. Morillo has escaped with his wife,

64
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:11,566
along with one of the influencers,
Jules Santos.

65
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:14,319
They managed to reach Alicante alive.

66
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:20,783
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

67
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,120
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

68
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:30,460
We need to tighten our security
across the entire island.

69
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:33,254
We must have eyes on every corner.

70
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,551
Stay on alert.

71
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:43,097
I'm sure police officers
are already on the island.

72
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:45,850
Why didn't Captain Jacinto alert us?

73
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:49,437
We can't rely on Captain Jacinto now.

74
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,897
Why?

75
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,106
What happened?

76
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:56,027
Lucas also reported that
he's in detention.

77
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:57,862
So we're doomed.

78
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:02,075
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:04:02,158 --> 00:04:04,786
So we've lost our protection?

80
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:11,251
[MUSIC SWELLS]

81
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:21,761
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:55,044
[DOMINGO] <i>I don't like wasting my time.</i>

83
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:59,340
All I want is for you to explain this.

84
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,343
Make me understand.

85
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,471
Why did they find this inside your house?!

86
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:06,431
[ENVELOPE SLAMS]

87
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:09,100
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,894
With all due respect, sir,

89
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,648
that money isn't mine.

90
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:25,158
Are you saying that two million pesos
just magically appeared in your house?

91
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:27,535
Cash?

92
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:34,334
[CHUCKLING]

93
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:37,462
Don't take me for a fool.

94
00:05:39,756 --> 00:05:43,217
Answer my question.

95
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,679
- [SLAMS]
- Where did you get that money?!

96
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:49,932
Someone is sabotaging me, sir.

97
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,645
They planted the money in my house.

98
00:05:56,355 --> 00:06:00,568
We suspect that you have a hand

99
00:06:00,651 --> 00:06:04,489
in what's happening in La Playa Roja.

100
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:07,909
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

101
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:10,411
We still have the hostages

102
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:13,998
and the VIPs of the resort.

103
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:16,084
They'll act as our protection.

104
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,881
- Dado.
- Sir?

105
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:24,842
Get one of the hostages
from the banquet hall.

106
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:31,015
Gwen, make sure the staff
stay in the stockroom.

107
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:33,017
Ian.

108
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:38,106
Connect all TV monitors to one source.

109
00:06:38,856 --> 00:06:40,274
That can be arranged, but…

110
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:42,443
[CLEARS THROAT] What for?

111
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:45,404
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

112
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:50,076
It's getting too boring for us
and the guests here at the resort.

113
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:54,288
We need to entertain them.

114
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:55,581
Yes, sir.

115
00:06:55,665 --> 00:07:02,672
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:12,348
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

117
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,561
[EMIL] <i>Was it Magnus?</i>

118
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:19,480
<i>Is he hurting you?</i>

119
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:24,068
<i>How many times has this happened, huh?</i>

120
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:28,698
<i>Padua, get up.</i>

121
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,534
<i>Why? What do you want from me?</i>

122
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:34,829
<i>Just do as we say. Get up. Hurry!</i>

123
00:07:34,912 --> 00:07:41,919
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:47,675
[LOCKS RATTLING]

125
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:57,685
[CELL DOOR, LOCKS RATTLING]

126
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:09,989
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:12,909
[LOCKS RATTLING]

128
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:14,118
[LATCH CLANKS]

129
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:16,579
[METAL DOOR CREAKS]

130
00:08:21,792 --> 00:08:25,129
<i>Padua. Long time no see.</i>

131
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:28,424
<i>What do you want from me?</i>

132
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:30,676
[CHUCKLES]

133
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,137
<i>It's you who needs something from me.</i>

134
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:36,849
<i>Remember, you are charged with murder.</i>

135
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:41,979
<i>You killed a fellow cop</i>
<i>and got involved in drugs.</i>

136
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:45,191
<i>If you serve your sentence,</i>

137
00:08:45,274 --> 00:08:47,568
<i>you'll be dead before you get out of here.</i>

138
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,823
<i>I can help you.</i>

139
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:56,202
<i>In exchange…</i>

140
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,497
<i>I have a job for you.</i>

141
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,710
<i>We'll make big money there.</i>

142
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,463
<i>Their guests are all rich.</i>

143
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:10,883
<i>What we'll take from them</i>
<i>won't put a dent in their wallets.</i>

144
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:16,722
<i>It's time to make those bastards pay.</i>

145
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,058
<i>La Playa Roja?</i>

146
00:09:21,769 --> 00:09:23,896
<i>Magnus Roja's property?</i>

147
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,523
<i>You know him?</i>

148
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:27,984
<i>No.</i>

149
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:32,738
<i>But many people know that billionaire.</i>

150
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:39,829
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:44,625
<i>Sir.</i>

152
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:50,089
<i>That's my former fellow inmate,</i>
<i>Diosdado Menor,</i>

153
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,633
<i>an explosives expert.</i>

154
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:55,094
<i>He's one of the sharpest people I know.</i>

155
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:57,263
<i>He works clean.</i>

156
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:01,851
<i>Ian Menor, Dado's younger brother.</i>

157
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:04,979
<i>An expert when it comes to computers.</i>

158
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:09,191
<i>Lucas Esteban, another former inmate.</i>

159
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:12,403
<i>Ex-special forces.</i>

160
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:15,573
<i>He was stationed in Mindanao</i>
<i>for ten years.</i>

161
00:10:15,656 --> 00:10:17,074
<i>He's a veteran fighter.</i>

162
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:19,702
<i>He doesn't hesitate to kill. Right, Lucas?</i>

163
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:26,876
<i>That's Roberto Bobong Aguas,</i>
<i>Dado's recruit.</i>

164
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,544
<i>He's an arms expert.</i>

165
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:32,298
<i>He can use any kind of gun.</i>
<i>A sharpshooter.</i>

166
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:36,385
<i>I also recruited a martial arts expert.</i>

167
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,348
Hm.

168
00:10:44,226 --> 00:10:50,566
[DARK MUSIC SWELLS]

169
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:09,043
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:11:14,465 --> 00:11:21,389
[EXHAUST FAN WHIRRING]

171
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:28,437
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:42,660
[LOUD THUD FROM DISTANCE]

173
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:53,796
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:55,548
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

175
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,341
- [ICE] <i>Olsen!</i>
- [GROANS]

176
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,176
Olsen!

177
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,511
[MAGNUS] Wendy!

178
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:03,806
What's wrong?

179
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:05,057
Hm?

180
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,476
Sorry.

181
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,145
It was just a bad dream.

182
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,397
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,941
I see. Uh… go back to sleep.

184
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:17,570
They haven't returned yet.

185
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:25,369
I didn't mean for you and Greta to fight.

186
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:31,250
I shouldn't have told my son
about what happened.

187
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:34,920
I made a promise to your wife.

188
00:12:36,505 --> 00:12:39,216
I made a promise to my friend.

189
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:43,554
Don't blame yourself, Wendy.

190
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:47,725
Magnus.

191
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:52,062
Promise me you'll forgive Greta.

192
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:02,156
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:03,365
[MAGNUS SIGHS]

194
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:05,826
You're such a good friend.

195
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,166
You know I'm not.

196
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:18,631
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

197
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:26,555
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

198
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:27,640
You know what?

199
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:31,936
The first thing I'll do
once I get off this island

200
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:34,563
is treat Mama to grilled pork belly.

201
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:35,689
[OLSEN CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

202
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:39,193
We'll eat it with our hands.

203
00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:42,404
We'll also have pickled papaya
and spiced coconut vinegar.

204
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:47,117
I'll let her eat her heart out for once.

205
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:48,536
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

206
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:50,246
Why that specifically?

207
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:53,791
Because grilled pork belly
is her favorite.

208
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,168
But I usually forbid her from eating it

209
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:58,963
because she has high blood pressure.

210
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:02,132
Then you shouldn't feed her that.

211
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:04,468
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

212
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:05,761
Life is short.

213
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:11,183
Hey, don't worry too much, okay?

214
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,018
Yes, life is short, but…

215
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:16,230
we'll get through this. I promise.

216
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:20,651
I'll even go with you
to buy grilled pork belly.

217
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:22,111
The rice is on me.

218
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,905
Pfft! Just the rice?

219
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:28,033
Then I'll buy you
some soda too. [SNICKERS]

220
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,619
How about

221
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:31,704
dessert?

222
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:35,583
Hey, didn't you just say
your mom has high blood pressure?

223
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:37,459
The dessert is for me.

224
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:39,503
[OLSEN SIGHS] Fine. Dessert's on me too.

225
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:46,844
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:00,399
- Ice, run. Go--
- [GUNSHOTS]

227
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:01,609
Ah! Olsen!

228
00:15:02,192 --> 00:15:04,653
[GUNSHOTS]

229
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,114
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

230
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:18,375
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:36,560
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:38,520
[GRETA] <i>In a week's time, Wendy,</i>

233
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:40,147
<i>you'll finally be free.</i>

234
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:44,360
<i>It's been ten years, Greta.</i>

235
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:50,699
<i>Thank you for enduring this much.</i>

236
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,955
<i>But…</i>

237
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:58,707
<i>I have another favor I wanted to ask you.</i>

238
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:01,168
<i>What is it?</i>

239
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:05,464
<i>Can you</i>

240
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:09,551
<i>keep our agreement a secret?</i>

241
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:12,429
<i>Especially from Magnus.</i>

242
00:16:14,181 --> 00:16:15,599
<i>Of course.</i>

243
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:18,143
<i>But why?</i>

244
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:20,854
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

245
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:24,483
<i>If only you knew what we've been through.</i>

246
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:28,487
<i>Magnus and I almost separated.</i>

247
00:16:29,446 --> 00:16:30,823
<i>Many times.</i>

248
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:34,326
<i>But in the end,</i>

249
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,744
<i>we're still together.</i>

250
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:43,168
<i>Maybe that's what happens</i>
<i>when you truly love each other.</i>

251
00:16:44,628 --> 00:16:48,340
<i>I can't risk damaging</i>
<i>our relationship again, Wendy.</i>

252
00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:51,260
<i>And this…</i>

253
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,971
<i>This secret</i>

254
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:58,350
<i>might ruin my relationship with Magnus.</i>

255
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:02,896
<i>Greta,</i>

256
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,690
<i>you can trust me.</i>

257
00:17:05,816 --> 00:17:09,778
<i>I won't let that happen</i>
<i>to your relationship.</i>

258
00:17:12,656 --> 00:17:14,658
<i>Or our friendship.</i>

259
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:19,413
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:26,003
[LIAM] Careful.

261
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:30,549
[LUNA] What are you saying, bro?

262
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:32,593
What I'm saying is,

263
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:35,846
what if my anger has no basis?

264
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:40,851
What if he really had nothing to do with
all the things I'm blaming him for?

265
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:45,522
With everything I found out
about Mama,

266
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,693
I don't know what to believe.
I'm so confused.

267
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:51,904
What is the truth?

268
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:58,410
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:01,080
Can you do it?

270
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,336
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

271
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,840
- [EMIL] Ayen!
- Bro.

272
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,426
Ayen!

273
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:17,054
[LIAM] Shh, shh.

274
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,222
[EMIL] Ayen!

275
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:21,642
Ayen!

276
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:26,146
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,731
Ayen!

278
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:30,275
[EMIL] You walked out on me again!

279
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:36,990
This is for you!

280
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,536
For you and your sibling!

281
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,169
Bro.

282
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:53,340
I believe that everything will be fine.

283
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:55,592
We will be able to escape here alive.

284
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,263
Hmm?

285
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,598
- Let's go.
- Come on.

286
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:08,480
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:09,523
[LIAM GRUNTS] Hmph.

288
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,029
Come.

289
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,337
[EMIL] So? Did you see her?

290
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:34,214
[GOON] No, sir.

291
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:36,967
[EMIL] Look for her everywhere.

292
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,177
Don't stop searching.

293
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,095
Come. Let's go this way.

294
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:42,389
Ayen!

295
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:49,188
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:59,823
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:23,513
[LUNA] Hurry.

298
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:28,685
[WENDY] Magnus.

299
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:35,776
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:39,988
I should be out there, not Liam.

301
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,367
But you're also needed here

302
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,662
to take care of Greta.

303
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:55,003
I know how hard it is for a parent

304
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:58,173
not to know what's happening
to their child.

305
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:04,096
I trust God to keep them safe.

306
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:12,020
You know, Wendy,

307
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:14,106
I regret…

308
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:19,569
being a…

309
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:23,865
bad father and having
a bad relationship with Liam.

310
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:30,205
It's my fault for not believing in
what he wanted to do.

311
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,334
And in his capabilities.

312
00:21:36,044 --> 00:21:38,297
You know the bloody irony
of it all is that

313
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,632
it took a hostage situation happening

314
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:46,388
for me to see how lucky I am
to have a son like him.

315
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:50,183
I've seen your son.

316
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,313
He's brave.

317
00:21:55,188 --> 00:21:56,606
He's bold.

318
00:21:59,026 --> 00:22:00,569
Despite everything,

319
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:05,324
you and Greta were able
to raise him to be a good man.

320
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:08,327
You know, Wendy,

321
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:09,995
while you were in jail,

322
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:15,625
Chief Ben was a good guardian to Olsen.

323
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,794
You were too.

324
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:22,883
Olsen told me a lot about you.

325
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:26,887
You and Papa

326
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:30,724
acted as Olsen's fathers.

327
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:35,270
Thank you so much, Magnus.

328
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:42,027
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

329
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:44,404
I'm sorry, Wendy.

330
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:47,908
I'm truly sorry that

331
00:22:49,284 --> 00:22:51,828
you didn't get the chance

332
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:56,333
to be with your son
while he was growing up.

333
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:01,088
It's all because of Greta.

334
00:23:01,671 --> 00:23:03,006
Magnus.

335
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:07,511
Wendy.

336
00:23:08,261 --> 00:23:09,679
I admire you.

337
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:14,684
The sacrifices you made for Olsen.

338
00:23:16,436 --> 00:23:17,521
Your

339
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:21,691
unconditional love for him.

340
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:26,822
For being a good mom

341
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:29,241
and a good person.

342
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,576
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY, SNIFFLES]

343
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:38,458
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

344
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:52,305
[MUSIC BECOMES STIRRING]

345
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:57,394
Come on.

346
00:24:09,489 --> 00:24:10,574
[LUNA] Dude.

347
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:12,367
Let's rest for two minutes.

348
00:24:13,118 --> 00:24:14,161
Sure.

349
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:16,454
[BOTH PANTING]

350
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:19,916
[OLSEN] Let's go.

351
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:22,335
Careful.

352
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:42,731
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

353
00:24:55,118 --> 00:25:02,125
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

354
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:16,598
[GOON AND OLSEN GRUNTING]

355
00:25:19,434 --> 00:25:21,228
[GOON GROANS]

356
00:25:23,396 --> 00:25:24,314
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

357
00:25:36,993 --> 00:25:39,955
- [COCKS RIFLE]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

358
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:44,542
[ICE] Olsen! Olsen!

359
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:49,297
[BOTH GRUNTING]

360
00:25:52,509 --> 00:25:53,927
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

361
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:02,978
Ice?

362
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:06,898
- I'm sorry!
- It's okay. I'm okay.

363
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:08,566
Hey, hey, hey.

364
00:26:09,192 --> 00:26:10,568
Be strong, okay?

365
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:12,737
I'll keep you safe.

366
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:15,448
I promise. Come on.

367
00:26:20,161 --> 00:26:21,329
[CARIASO]
<i>Everyone, stay alert.</i>

368
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:24,249
[LIAM] <i>Would you do anything for</i>
<i>your family? Even if it's wrong?</i>

369
00:26:24,332 --> 00:26:30,297
[EMIL] <i>Even VIPs will get killed</i>
<i>if you don't do what we want!</i>

370
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:31,923
[TOPAK] <i>We're all going to die!</i>

371
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:34,092
<i>We can't just wait for their next move.</i>

372
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:35,885
<i>We need to rescue the hostages.</i>

373
00:26:35,969 --> 00:26:37,846
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

374
00:26:37,929 --> 00:26:39,347
[LUNA] <i>There are guards everywhere.</i>

375
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:40,890
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

376
00:26:40,974 --> 00:26:41,933
[GOON GRUNTS]

377
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:47,439
[LIAM] <i>When I come back,</i>
<i>I'll have our staff with me.</i>
